fields.title: About
fields.content:
About

Empowering learners worldwide to take control of their education

The K Network is an organization on with a specific purpose.  We are a not-for-profit with the goal of materially improving the way people learn by empowering learners worldwide to take control of their education.

Our foundational principle is the education should be freer and more easily accessible.  To that end, all of the site’s resources are available to anyone without cost.  Regardless of whether you are a student, parent, teacher, administrator, adult who is a life-long learner, home-schooler or have woken up after a deep 25 year slumber, The K Network wants you to have the ability, the tools, the motivation and the materials to be able to learn in a deeper, more fulfilling, more inspired way.  And all of the website’s resources are available to you free of charge.

How it works for students

Students can start a class and start adding subjects or topics to study, taking advantage of social learning tools such as peer to peer teaching and learnings, group dynamics like when you are on a soccer team and resume-based credentialing for performing teaching and learning-based tasks.

How it works for coaches, parents and teachers

Those individuals who are helping students learn can also start a class and start adding subjects or topics to study.  As a coach, parent or teacher, you can assign “buckets” of topics to the students they are working with, have teams of students work together and support each other while becoming proficient in topics and completing tasks, and track the progress of your class in real time.

Existing Content

For mathematics, our platform sits on top of Khan Academy’s 345+ interactive exercises, turning single person Khan Academy into Group Khan Academy.

Future Content

For English, The K Network is building a “Complete a Writing Task” application, which will allow teachers to create a writing task, to assign it to students, to break that task down into its component steps and to track the completion of each step, giving teachers who assign writing tasks (English and Language Arts, Social Studies and Sciences) real time tracking of the progress their students make from the day the writing task is assigned to the day that it is handed in.

For all other subjects, The K Network has grand ambitions, but will take one step at a time.

A world of skills to practice, with help along the way

Using Khan Academy, Practice math at your own pace with our adaptive assessment environment. You can start at 1+1 and work your way into calculus or jump right into whatever topic needs some brushing up.

Each problem is randomly generated, so you never run out of practice material. If you need a hint, every single problem can be broken down, step-by-step, with one click. If you need more help, you can always watch a related video

fields.title: Meet the Team
fields.content:
Team

A focused team working on something big.

We are just getting going but have infectious enthusiasm around having students enjoying learning more and around getting students better results in their education.  Too many people around the world are stuck not being able to decide for themselves the quality of their education, or they are being forced to spend their learning time (i.e. school) in a way that doesn’t give them the best and most productive setting for both having fun and enjoying the learning process.  We think the technology exists today to fundamentally change this, so we are building the tools and resources we think every student should have at their fingertips.

We believe a few great people can change the world and the world of education.  We are focused on hiring the very best – people who are enthusiastic, intelligent and creative.  We believe it is our obligation to relentlessly keep connected to what learners need to achieve their education goals, and we make every decision with the learner, or student, in mind.
